  "text": "The GTM method has been successfully applied in PET brain imaging, resulting in biases of less than 10% in the estimation of striatal uptake [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Its applicability to tumor imaging is severely restricted by the required delineation process, which can be very challenging (Fig. 12) , and by the assumption of a piecewise constant activity distribution. It may still be worth investigating the use of the GTM method for local correction when a tumor is close to more than one compartment (for instance, a lung tumor close to the liver). In that specific circumstance (Fig. 6) , it may yield more accurate results than the RC method.",
